name: Daniel Penny
summary: Daniel Penny, a former NYPD officer, was acquitted of manslaughter charges in the death of Jordan Neely, a homeless man who died in 2018 after Penny placed him in a chokehold on a New York City subway train. The family of Jordan Neely has filed a civil suit against Penny.

name: Nani
summary: Former Manchester United star Nani has announced his retirement from professional football at the age of 38. The Portuguese winger had an illustrious career spanning 19 years, representing clubs like Manchester United, Sporting Lisbon, and Orlando City. Nani made his professional debut for Sporting Lisbon in 2003 and moved to Manchester United in 2007, where he won four Premier League titles, two League Cups, and a Champions League title. He later returned to Sporting Lisbon and also played for Fenerbahce, Valencia, Lazio, Almeria, and Orlando City. Nani has also represented Portugal at the international level, earning 112 caps and scoring 24 goals. In an emotional retirement announcement, Nani expressed gratitude for his journey and reflected on his achievements and the unforgettable memories he created throughout his career.
